<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="OTA2">
<l>eṉṟu kaṭalkaṭainta tevvulaka nīrēṟṟa</l>
<l>toṉṟu mataṉai yuṇarēṉā – ṉaṉṟa</l>
<l>taṭaittuṭaittuk kaṇpaṭutta vāḻi yitunī</l>
<l>paṭaittiṭan tuṇṭumiḻnta pār</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When was the ocean churned?<note>One of the figures of speech which expresses the devotees’ amazement at the sight of their god’s creative powers is a rhetorical question, here directed towards the deeds performed by Nārāyaṇa and Varāha.</note>  Which earth did you receive along with water?</l>
<l>Not even one thing I do understand. On that day that was the ocean</l>
<l>you blocked, burst [and on which] you closed [your] eyes, this</l>
<l>is the earth you created, dug up, ate [and] spit out.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
